OL,3,C'I wanted to give up': Sexual assault
OL,4,Csurvivor speaks about the court process
OL,6,FNatalie has told ITV Border that
OL,7,Fdespite the "long and drawn out"
OL,8,Fprocess, she has no regrets about
OL,9,Fcoming forward and would encourage
OL,10,Fothers to do the same.
OL,12,FThe assault happened when Natalie was
OL,13,Fenjoying a drink after work. Dea, a
OL,14,Fregular at the bar, started to touch
OL,15,Fher.
OL,17,FWhile a member of bar staff told him
OL,18,Fto stop, Dea continued to grope
OL,19,FNatalie for the rest of the night.
