OL,3,C'I wanted to give up': Sexual assault
OL,4,Csurvivor speaks about the court process
OL,6,FMs Brindley said: "It's so common that
OL,7,Fpeople are waiting sometimes years
OL,8,Fbetween reporting to police and the
OL,9,Fcase getting to court. And that can
OL,10,Fadd so much trauma to someone going
OL,11,Fthrough that process. People say to us
OL,12,Fit's like their life is on hold.
OL,14,F"Delays in court cases were bad before
OL,15,FCovid, but they're even worse now in
OL,16,Fterms of the backlog. It definitely
OL,17,Fdeters people from reporting.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/9
